observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
a. Municipal Treasurer (MT) to prepare a list of its individual taxpayers with delinquencies for CY 2001 and below and another list for CYs 2002 to 2019 as of December 31, 2019 and furnish it to the Municipal Accountant;
b. Municipal Accountant to facilitate the adjustment of RPT/SET Receivables once the list is received from the MT;
c. Municipal Accountant to ensure that all collections are properly recorded;
d. Municipal Assessor to facilitate the immediate cleansing of property tax records to have a reliable Real Property Tax Assessment Roll and thereafter, a reliable RPT and SET Receivables accounts; and
e. MT to continue the enforcement of the remedies as provided in RA No. 7160.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
 Inventory Committee to complete the physical inventory of all property of the Municipality and prepare and submit immediately the pertinent inventory reports;
 MGSO and Municipal Accountant to reconcile their records;
 Municipal General Services Officer (MGSO) to prepare and maintain complete and updated property cards, PAR and renew the same every three years; and
 MGSO to submit the Inventory and Inspection Report for Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) and its supporting documents to the Audit Team and constantly monitor the status of physical inventory taking to ensure its completion and submission of complete RPCPPE.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
 Appraisal Committee/Team to properly appraise the donated land as to their fair values at the time of acquisition and apply the same to the purchased land if the acquisition costs cannot be determined reliably;
 Municipal Accountant to record the land once the fair value are established and copy of titles are received;
 Municipal Assessor to submit the Schedule of Land to the Audit Team for verification and in compliance with Section 111 of PD No. 1445; and
 Municipal Assessor to ensure that all land owned by the Municipality are declared in the name of the Municipality.
We also recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the MGSO to request from the RD regarding the owner’s copy of title for the six parcels of land and expedite the titling of eight parcels of land owned by the Municipality.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
a. Municipal Accountant in coordination with the BAC Chairman to submit the lacking supporting documents to the Audit Team for further evaluation of the paid procurement transactions;
b. BAC Chairman to ensure that the Notice of Award (NOA) and Notice to Proceed (NTP) are duly received by the Contractor;
c. BAC Chairman to ensure strict compliance with the documentary requirements to substantiate the correct procurement activities of the Municipality; and
d. Municipal Accountant to ensure that the Disbursement Voucher is supported with proper and complete documents before processing its payment.

